message_1:
How can we design a heat exchanger for a specific process that involves the transfer of heat from a hot gas stream to a cool liquid stream, while maintaining a maximum temperature difference of 20°C and a maximum pressure drop of 2 bar, given the following specifications: 
- Hot gas stream flow rate = 50 kg/hr, specific heat capacity = 0.4 kJ/kg°C, and inlet temperature = 150°C;
- Cool liquid stream flow rate = 100 kg/hr, specific heat capacity = 4.2 kJ/kg°C, and inlet temperature = 25°C; 
- Overall heat transfer coefficient = 500 W/m2K, and thermal conductivity of the heat exchanger material = 100 W/mK.
Please select the most suitable type of heat exchanger and calculate the required heat transfer area and the length of the tube.
